column5: Hey just wondering if there is anything kicking around right now at the fishermans pier under the skyway? Thanks
I've heard that there's carp, salmon, and trout hanging around the peir as well as sheepshead cruising the walls of the pier. Would there also be walleye, bass, pike, etc. present?

I wouldn't expect too many guys to post openly about whether they're doing well or not off the pier....just too easy to get to, and who likes to share a spot when the fishing's good?  I would recommend heading down there and checking it out...if we don't hear from you, we'll know you're doing well   I wouldn't expect too much in the walleye department....mayyyyybe the odd bass or pike....
the fishfinder goes crazy under the bridge there every time i go under it. the rod, not so much.

I was down there today, I didn't catch any thing but I was talking to an older gentlemen and he Was  telling me that he catches fish very often there he showed me a pic of a 16lbs salmon he caught a few days ago.
